    "remarks": {
      "sha256": "5df43735127ed9bc3b2ef7332fadcd2f3097539a63fc125bb795143fb5684ada",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "It is not even known whether $h(n)\\geq 2$ for all large $n$.\n\nSee also [99]."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "ff242979037a2ffa667e4ba487d3676fe3b6dd95d672caf5eaa38725917f54f0",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Let $h(n)$ count the number of incongruent sets of $n$ points in $\\mathbb{R}^2$ which minimise the diameter subject to the constraint that $d(x,y)\\geq 1$ for all points $x\\neq y$. Is it true that $h(n)\\to \\infty$?"
    }
  },
